<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When using the new Zend_Loader_AutoloaderFactory with ClassMap Autoloader before the Standard Autoloader, the application falls over with the error:</p>

<pre class="literal">
Autoloader class "Zend_Loader_ClassMapAutoloader" not loaded
</pre>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
include 'Zend/Loader/AutoloaderFactory.php';
 $config = array(
        'Zend_Loader_ClassMapAutoloader' =&gt; array(
            './library/autoload_classmap.php',
            './application/autoload_classmap.php'
        ),
        'Zend_Loader_StandardAutoloader' =&gt; array(
            'prefixes' =&gt; array(
                'My_'       =&gt; 'My',
                'Zend_'     =&gt; 'Zend',
                'ZendX_'    =&gt; 'ZendX',
            ),
            'fallback_autoloader' =&gt; true,
        ),
    );

    Zend_Loader_AutoloaderFactory::factory($config);
</code></pre>

<p>Adding the following:</p>

<pre class="literal">
include 'Zend/Loader/ClassMapAutoloader.php';
</pre>

<p>before the</p>

<pre class="literal">
Zend_Loader_AutoloaderFactory::factory($config);
</pre>

<p>line fixes the issue.</p>

